EL PASO, TEXAS
US / MEXICO BORDER

04:52.262 --> 04:57.541
Georgina! Obey me.
I will love you. Come on.

04:58.222 --> 05:00.690
- That's how it works, huh?
- That's right.

05:08.302 --> 05:10.657
She got a sister?

05:11.542 --> 05:13.533
How's business?

05:14.742 --> 05:17.575
The Japanese are here in a big way.

05:18.582 --> 05:25.260
Cheap labour, factory space, but they feel
a lot safer living over the border in El Paso.

05:25.342 --> 05:30.211
I ferry them back and forth.
They think I'm John Wayne.

05:34.462 --> 05:37.613
- I live like a king down here.
- Yes, you do.

05:41.022 --> 05:44.173
- You been workin'?
- Yeah. No.

05:44.262 --> 05:48.733
No. I've been movin' around. You know.
Colombia, a couple of places I can't name.

05:48.822 --> 05:51.973
Nothin' catches my fancy.

05:54.982 --> 05:58.338
You think God'll forgive us
for what we've done?

05:58.422 --> 06:00.538
- No.
- You don't?

06:00.622 --> 06:01.896
Me either.

06:04.062 --> 06:08.817
- How long you stayin'?
- I don't know, I just... you know.

06:08.902 --> 06:12.736
I wanted to see you, Ray,
see how you're doin'.

06:12.822 --> 06:15.290
I just came by on impulse.

06:15.382 --> 06:17.816
I could do with some impulse.

06:28.262 --> 06:30.253
What happened?

06:31.382 --> 06:37.537
Family paid the ransom, then they
sent the kid home after a couple of days.

06:37.622 --> 06:39.692
Minus an ear, of course.

06:39.782 --> 06:43.331
Now every mother in Mexico City
with money wants bigger bodyguards.

06:43.422 --> 06:47.540
- My own wife included.
- I hate to break it to you, but she's right.

06:47.622 --> 06:49.931
She's right.

06:50.022 --> 06:54.254
Look, Sammy, all my clients
have kidnap and ransom insurance.

06:54.342 --> 06:57.459
I have a policy.
AIG. My dad gave it to me.

06:57.542 --> 07:00.295
Yeah, I know. I got it for your dad.

07:00.382 --> 07:04.853
But what'll you do in 60 days when you can't
renew it because you have no bodyguard?

07:04.942 --> 07:07.695
I know. I had to let Emilio go.

07:07.782 --> 07:12.697
Well, you gotta please Lisa.
I mean, ass like that's hard to find.

07:13.702 --> 07:15.693
Look.

07:15.782 --> 07:20.902
A bodyguard's like anything else.
You get what you pay for, OK?

07:20.982 --> 07:23.815
You could do this.
Get one that's got a decent résumé.

07:23.902 --> 07:27.861
We're not lookin' for goddamn Superman,
right? Get someone cheap.

07:27.942 --> 07:34.290
So you renew the policy, and then
fire the prick for whatever - incompetence.

07:34.382 --> 07:38.853
All kidding aside, the most important thing
is that your daughter goes back to school,

07:38.942 --> 07:41.775
and that your wife gets to save face.

07:41.862 --> 07:48.097
This way you won't be the only
unprotected family in the neighbourhood.

07:57.942 --> 08:01.935
That's right, a bodyguard.
Your Spanish is good enough.

08:02.022 --> 08:04.980
- You're crazy.
- You even look the part.

08:05.062 --> 08:06.973
In my state, I couldn't guard a corpse.

08:07.062 --> 08:10.896
It's rich guys flashing their cash.
It's all for show. Nothing's gonna happen.

08:10.982 --> 08:15.294
Yeah? You think they'd
hire a drunk, a has-been?

08:16.622 --> 08:18.772
You have to keep it under control.

08:20.102 --> 08:24.732
What ifthere was, you know... just, say,
a kidnapping attempt? What do I do then?

08:24.822 --> 08:29.498
You do your best. They're not gonna be
paying you enough to perform miracles.

08:29.582 --> 08:33.813
It's not exactly a scam, Crease.
Even at half speed, you're pretty damn good.

08:33.902 --> 08:37.496
Yeah. A bodyguard's gotta
be close to people, though.

08:37.582 --> 08:40.494
They talk all the time.
You know I'm no good at that.

08:40.582 --> 08:44.461
You'll be the silent type.
They're gonna appreciate that.

08:51.702 --> 08:53.897
Bodyguard. So who's the guy?

08:53.982 --> 08:56.655
Samuel Ramos. He's a young guy.

08:56.742 --> 09:00.860
- He owns one ofthe plants in Juàrez.
- Yeah?

09:00.942 --> 09:03.297
The Jap car industry is in the toilet.

09:03.382 --> 09:06.658
He's trying to persuade Ford
to partner with him.

09:06.742 --> 09:10.417
I think he's in trouble.
His family lives in Mexico City.

09:10.502 --> 09:14.290
He asked me if I knew anybody he could trust.

09:14.382 --> 09:17.260
- And you thought of me?
- Yeah.

09:17.342 --> 09:20.732
Take ajob, Crease. Breathe some air.

09:20.822 --> 09:22.972
Then decide ifyou want to stick around.

09:23.062 --> 09:27.180
Besides, I'm glad to see you, you know?
I got nobody to talk to down here.

09:34.462 --> 09:39.252
Listen, my wife wants
someone presentable and polite.

09:39.342 --> 09:42.732
You'll be the fifth candidate
she sees this week.

09:42.822 --> 09:44.494
Your résumé's quite impressive.

09:44.582 --> 09:48.939
16 years of military experience,
extensive counter-terrorism work.

09:49.022 --> 09:52.298
I'm surprised anybody could afford you.
What's the catch?

09:52.382 --> 09:54.498
I drink.

09:54.582 --> 09:56.573
How does that affect you?

09:59.062 --> 10:01.098
Coordination, reaction time.

10:01.182 --> 10:04.572
Iftop professionals try to kidnap
your daughter, I'll do the best I can,

10:04.662 --> 10:07.051
but the service will be on a par with the pay.

10:08.982 --> 10:10.893
What if amateurs try it?

10:10.982 --> 10:14.179
I'd probably kill 'em. Is that likely?

10:14.262 --> 10:16.059
No.

10:16.142 --> 10:21.170
No one is to know about your drinking.
That includes my wife.

10:45.462 --> 10:47.453
Lisa!

10:49.382 --> 10:51.373
Lisa!

11:02.822 --> 11:05.859
My wife Lisa.
And this is John Creasy.

11:11.582 --> 11:13.777
- You're an American.
- So are you.

11:15.102 --> 11:16.501
It's all in there.

11:21.262 --> 11:24.937
- Would you like a drink?
- Yes. Jack and water would be good.

11:26.222 --> 11:28.577
Have you done much of
this kind ofwork before?

11:28.662 --> 11:29.777
No, ma'am.

11:29.862 --> 11:33.537
But he has a lot of experience
in related fields.

11:35.822 --> 11:38.541
- Do you have a family, Mr Creasy?
- No.

11:39.062 --> 11:41.451
Pita? Pita.

11:45.102 --> 11:47.935
- Yes, Mom?
- Honey, this is Mr Creasy.

11:50.022 --> 11:52.775
Buenas tardes, señor Creasy.
Mucho gusto en conocerle.

11:52.862 --> 11:57.652
It's English, honey. Do you wanna
show Mr Creasy to his room?

11:57.742 --> 12:00.097
- This way, Mr Creasy.
- OK.

12:09.422 --> 12:11.538
Thank you.

12:18.142 --> 12:19.461
Just like that?

12:20.862 --> 12:25.697
I think it's nice that he's an American.

12:25.782 --> 12:29.855
I think it's terrific. Are you sure?

12:32.382 --> 12:34.179
Thank you.

12:34.502 --> 12:36.060
Thank you.

12:37.062 --> 12:39.053
I feel better now.

12:41.502 --> 12:44.096
- !Hola, Bruno!
- Buenas tardes.

12:44.182 --> 12:48.653
That's Bruno, the gardener.
And that's Maria, the cook.

12:48.742 --> 12:51.495
- !Hola, Maria!
- Hola, Pita.

12:53.622 --> 12:57.535
We fixed the room up two weeks ago.
It's nicer than before.

13:00.462 --> 13:04.250
You've got a TV and a CD player.
What kind of music do you like, Mr Creasy?

13:04.342 --> 13:07.857
- I don't know.
- You don't know?

13:07.942 --> 13:10.695
I don't know.

13:10.782 --> 13:15.173
That's Bird. Emilio forgot
to take him when he left.

13:16.182 --> 13:18.457
Emilio was my last bodyguard.

13:20.342 --> 13:24.415
Have you protected
a lot of children before, Mr Creasy?

13:24.502 --> 13:28.097
Creasy. You can call me Creasy.
And no, you're the first.

13:28.182 --> 13:29.934
Creasy.

13:30.022 --> 13:32.217
Bye, Creasy.

13:34.662 --> 13:36.459
Bye, Bird.

13:45.782 --> 13:50.617
- School tomorrow, Peeps.
- Does that mean we can get a dog?

13:50.702 --> 13:53.057
Dad promised me one
when I went back to school.

13:53.142 --> 13:55.212
Yeah, we'll see.

13:55.302 --> 14:00.092
Ifyou get a dog, will you give up your bear?
You're getting too old for him.

14:02.822 --> 14:08.340
- How did you like Mr Creasy?
- Creasy. He said to call him just Creasy.

14:08.422 --> 14:12.301
- That isn't disrespectful, is it?
- No, not if he asked you.

14:12.382 --> 14:15.180
Here. There you go.

14:22.742 --> 14:24.698
He's like a bear, too.

14:25.542 --> 14:27.658
- Yeah?
- A big, sad bear.

14:29.942 --> 14:33.696
- Is he sad?
- I think. Or something.

14:37.982 --> 14:39.973
Good night, honey.

14:41.982 --> 14:44.496
Can you get me some floss in the morning?

14:44.582 --> 14:46.459
- Floss?
- Yeah, the strawberry kind.

14:46.542 --> 14:48.294
Sure.

14:51.222 --> 14:53.213
Good night, Bear.

14:54.222 --> 14:56.213
Creasy Bear.

15:28.182 --> 15:32.494
- What's that one for?
- La Virgen de Guadalupe.

15:32.582 --> 15:36.257
Business. For Toyota, for Ford.

15:36.342 --> 15:41.621
If one dies, maybe she can
resurrect the other one. I don't know.

15:43.822 --> 15:45.813
She likes him.

15:46.742 --> 15:49.654
- What are you talkin' about?
- Creasy.

15:51.102 --> 15:53.093
Pita likes him.

15:54.542 --> 16:00.651
Pita loves school. Pita would love Count
Dracula if he took her back there, honey.

16:00.742 --> 16:02.539
OK?

16:04.342 --> 16:06.936
Hey. Are you OK?

16:07.022 --> 16:09.377
- I don't know.
- OK?

16:11.622 --> 16:15.137
I don't know, Lisa. I'm trying.

17:09.142 --> 17:10.939
Come on, Bird.

17:11.021 --> 17:13.855
That's right, that's right. Come on.

17:13.942 --> 17:15.614
All right.

17:15.702 --> 17:17.532
Home to Emilio.

17:18.462 --> 17:20.373
You're home free, baby.

17:39.622 --> 17:42.295
- Where are you from, Creasy?
- The US.

17:42.382 --> 17:45.215
- I know, but which state?
- No state in particular.

17:45.302 --> 17:52.652
- You can drive and talk at the same time.
- No, I can't, Pita, so please let me do myjob.

17:52.742 --> 17:54.380
Are you going to stay?

17:55.742 --> 18:00.372
My last bodyguard left. Somebody
gave him more money than we could.

18:00.462 --> 18:04.250
I guess that makes me a bargain, then, huh?

18:04.342 --> 18:09.291
Being black. Is that a positive or a negative
for a bodyguard in Mexico?

18:09.382 --> 18:11.498
Time will tell.

18:13.942 --> 18:17.901
There were 24 kidnappings in Mexico City
in the last six days.

18:17.982 --> 18:20.450
- Four a day.
- Yeah? 24?

18:20.542 --> 18:24.171
- 24. What do you think about that?
- I think you know more than you should.

18:24.262 --> 18:26.014
Well, thank you.

18:53.102 --> 18:55.821
- See you later.
- You have to sign.

18:55.902 --> 18:59.133
- What?
- You have to sign in. Show them your ID.

18:59.222 --> 19:01.213
- Buenos dias.
- Buenos dias.

19:01.302 --> 19:02.576
Come on.

19:03.782 --> 19:05.454
Right there.

19:05.542 --> 19:08.136
- Hola, Manuel.
- Hola, Pita.

19:17.742 --> 19:20.302
- !Hola, Pita!
- !Hola!

19:20.742 --> 19:24.018
Pita! It's so good to have you back.

19:24.102 --> 19:27.299
Sister Anna,
this is my new bodyguard, Creasy.

19:27.382 --> 19:31.295
- Sister Anna, the headmistress.
- Señor Creasy.

19:32.502 --> 19:36.700
- Hurry. Class is about to begin. Go, go.
- Bye, Creasy.

19:36.782 --> 19:37.851
Madre.

19:37.942 --> 19:41.378
You must look after our Pita.
It is not good that she is late today.

19:41.462 --> 19:45.740
I'm very sorry. I have to get used to
the routes. It won't happen again.

19:45.822 --> 19:49.417
No offence, but I regret that
your profession needs to exist.

19:49.502 --> 19:52.460
So do I, Madre, so do I.

19:52.542 --> 19:56.137
Do you ever see the hand of God
in what you do?

19:57.742 --> 19:59.733
No, not for a long time.

19:59.822 --> 20:02.575
The Bible says, "Be not overcome of evil..."

20:02.662 --> 20:06.701
"But overcome evil with good."

20:06.782 --> 20:09.535
That's Romans Chapter 12 Verse 21.

20:12.382 --> 20:15.294
I am the sheep that got lost, Madre.

21:16.062 --> 21:20.260
When you were a kid, Creasy,
did you like school?

21:20.342 --> 21:22.617
- I don't remember.
- You don't remember?

21:22.702 --> 21:26.456
No, I don't remember.
No, I didn't like it.

21:26.542 --> 21:28.737
Why not?

21:28.822 --> 21:33.134
Because it wasn't a school like yours, Pita.
There was no Sister Anna.

21:35.702 --> 21:37.977
Were you unhappy?

21:40.022 --> 21:43.332
Being unhappy, that's a state of mind.
I really don't remember.

21:52.342 --> 21:54.617
What happened to your hand?

21:55.942 --> 21:57.660
- It's a birth defect.
- No, it's not.

21:57.742 --> 21:59.175
Look, no more questions, OK?

22:01.942 --> 22:05.651
- It really wasn't a question.
- It sounded like a question to me.

22:06.902 --> 22:09.052
No, gracias. Gracias, no, no.

22:09.142 --> 22:11.417
Listen to me.
I'm being paid to protect you.

22:11.502 --> 22:12.491
No, no, no.

22:12.582 --> 22:15.972
I'm being paid to be your bodyguard.
Look at me.

22:16.502 --> 22:22.577
I'm not being paid to be your friend, but
to protect you. So no more questions, period.

22:24.462 --> 22:25.975
- Do you hear me?
- Yes.

22:28.662 --> 22:31.176
- No crying.
- I'm not crying.

22:32.182 --> 22:34.218
Well, don't start.

22:34.302 --> 22:37.658
You gotta understand, this is ajob.
In order for me to do myjob...

22:40.222 --> 22:42.417
Wait a minute.

23:28.742 --> 23:30.733
Yeah, come in.

23:36.102 --> 23:38.093
Mr Creasy.

23:38.782 --> 23:41.615
I just wanted to make sure
you have everything you need.

23:41.702 --> 23:43.101
I'm fine, thanks.

23:44.662 --> 23:48.974
Is the food all right?
Because Maria told me you didn't eat.

23:50.502 --> 23:55.053
Yeah, the food is great.
I just wasn't that hungry tonight.

23:57.422 --> 23:59.982
So you read the Bible?

24:00.782 --> 24:03.421
Yeah, sometimes.

24:03.502 --> 24:05.538
Does it help?

24:05.622 --> 24:07.260
Yeah, sometimes.

24:09.422 --> 24:12.494
- Can I talk to you for a minute?
- Sure.

24:14.422 --> 24:17.255
How are you doing with Pita?

24:17.342 --> 24:18.855
Fine.

24:18.942 --> 24:22.332
As soon as she figures out that
I'm not her new toy, it'll be fine.

24:22.422 --> 24:24.811
- She told me about that.
- OK.

24:26.302 --> 24:29.533
- You don't have children, do you?
- I told you I didn't.

24:29.622 --> 24:32.455
Well, they can be tenacious
when they want something.

24:32.542 --> 24:35.056
And Pitajust wants to be friends.

24:35.142 --> 24:36.734
OK.

24:36.822 --> 24:42.101
But you're paying me to protect her,
not to be her friend, right?

24:43.542 --> 24:45.533
So...

24:46.782 --> 24:49.171
Look, maybe this isn't gonna work out.

24:49.262 --> 24:54.256
Maybe your husband should find
somebody that's a little more sociable.

24:56.542 --> 24:57.861
No, you're right.

25:00.302 --> 25:02.941
You're being paid to protect her.

25:03.022 --> 25:06.412
And I'm confident that you'll do that.

25:10.702 --> 25:15.492
I'll be coming with you tomorrow.
I hope that's all right.

25:43.382 --> 25:46.499
You think God'll forgive us
for what we've done?

26:11.102 --> 26:14.890
I'm tired of killin', Ray.
I'm tired of killin', Ray.

26:17.742 --> 26:22.020
You think God'll forgive us
for what we've done?

26:22.102 --> 26:24.218
In my state, I couldn't...

26:24.302 --> 26:26.338
I couldn't guard a corpse.

26:26.422 --> 26:28.333
They talk all the time.

26:28.422 --> 26:31.141
You know I'm no good at that.

26:31.502 --> 26:34.221
You know I'm no good at that.

26:35.382 --> 26:37.134
You know how they say...

26:38.862 --> 26:41.740
a bullet always tells the truth?

27:21.262 --> 27:22.980
Yeah?

27:23.062 --> 27:25.212
- Hey.
- Crease.

27:25.302 --> 27:26.894
What's wrong?

27:26.982 --> 27:32.818
Hey, listen, you ever have
a 9mm round that didn't go off?

27:32.902 --> 27:35.416
Yeah. Failure to fire.

27:35.502 --> 27:38.539
I know, failure to fire and...

27:38.622 --> 27:43.457
You know, I pulled the trigger
and click - nothing.

27:43.542 --> 27:47.820
- You're talkin' about a bad primer.
- Yeah, yeah, but I...

27:47.902 --> 27:52.453
Yeah, right. Dimple on the primer.
That may be...

27:52.542 --> 27:54.817
Well, like we used to say...

27:56.102 --> 27:58.775
a bullet always tells the truth.

28:05.582 --> 28:08.335
Crease? You all right?

28:08.422 --> 28:10.094
Yeah.

28:11.102 --> 28:13.411
What were you shootin' at?

28:13.502 --> 28:15.697
Yeah, I'm sorry, Ray. I'm sorry I woke you.

28:15.782 --> 28:19.661
No, it's OK, it's nothin'. I was watchin' TV.

28:21.462 --> 28:23.453
OK.

29:39.822 --> 29:42.336
Pita, you have a pencil?

29:46.622 --> 29:48.214
Thank you.

30:20.542 --> 30:25.252
- It's hard to get used to the traffic down here.
- Yeah. I'm very sorry.

30:45.062 --> 30:47.098
- See you, baby.
- See you later.

30:47.182 --> 30:51.334
- Hey, don't forget your towel.
- Thank you.

30:56.622 --> 30:58.419
Bye.

32:01.382 --> 32:04.215
- You're a strong swimmer.
- I never win.

32:09.902 --> 32:11.699
Thanks.

32:14.862 --> 32:17.456
So, what do I do?

32:17.542 --> 32:20.898
You're the fastest in the water,
the slowest offthe blocks.

32:20.982 --> 32:23.257
What do you think that means?
What you gotta do?

32:23.342 --> 32:26.334
- Get faster offthe blocks?
- Get faster offthe blocks.

32:27.302 --> 32:29.611
- Our big swim meet is in three weeks.
- Yeah?

32:29.702 --> 32:35.220
- I was gonna enter the 150 freestyle.
- You'll be fine. You'll be OK.

32:36.862 --> 32:39.137
- I'll still be slow.
- You're not slow.

32:39.222 --> 32:44.216
- I never finish better than third.
- Then maybe you are slow.

32:46.782 --> 32:49.933
With us this evening we have
Mariana Guerrero from Reforma newspaper

32:50.022 --> 32:52.297
to speak with us about the kidnappings.

32:53.382 --> 32:56.499
Who are the ones responsible
for the kidnappings in Mexico?

32:56.582 --> 33:00.177
It is an activity of organised crime.
It's not a random kidnapping.

33:00.262 --> 33:02.378
They are not political kidnappings
like in Colombia.

33:02.462 --> 33:04.612
!Vamos, Bird!

33:04.702 --> 33:06.693
!Vamos!

33:12.182 --> 33:14.776
How do you think he got out?

33:16.342 --> 33:17.661
I let him go.

33:17.742 --> 33:21.257
- It's better to be free, right?
- It's better for him.

33:22.902 --> 33:25.735
Actually, he was driving me crazy.

33:29.182 --> 33:31.013
Good night.

33:35.942 --> 33:37.694
Good night.

33:52.302 --> 33:55.100
- See you in a couple of days, OK? I love you.
- Love you.

33:55.182 --> 33:56.979
Be good. Come on, Lise.

33:57.062 --> 34:00.418
All right, sweetheart,
so we'll call you from Detroit, OK?

34:01.222 --> 34:03.292
- I love you.
- Love you.

34:03.382 --> 34:05.418
- OK, bye.
- Señora, su café.

34:05.502 --> 34:07.413
Gracias.

34:07.502 --> 34:11.699
- OK, bye, honey. I love you!
- Love you.

34:16.542 --> 34:18.293
I hate leaving her.

34:31.302 --> 34:33.452
Concentrating?

34:33.542 --> 34:35.533
Eyes are closed?

34:39.621 --> 34:41.340
- What happened?
- I flinched.

34:41.422 --> 34:43.731
The gunshot holds no fear. Say it.

34:43.822 --> 34:47.098
- The gunshot holds no fear.
- The gunshot holds no fear! Say it!

34:47.181 --> 34:48.820
- The gunshot holds no fear.
- Louder!

34:48.902 --> 34:51.052
- The gunshot holds no fear!
- Louder!

34:51.141 --> 34:54.612
- The gunshot holds no fear!
- That's good. You welcome the sound.

34:54.702 --> 34:56.737
In fact, it's the sound that sets you free.

34:56.822 --> 35:01.020
You are a prisoner on this block until
that sound sets you free. Are you ready?

35:01.102 --> 35:03.696
- Yes.
- Are you ready? Are you set?

35:11.422 --> 35:13.413
Creasy?

35:13.502 --> 35:15.732
What's a concubine?

35:15.822 --> 35:18.973
- Why do you ask?
- It's in my history book.

35:19.982 --> 35:23.611
- It's like a wife, right?
- Yeah, yeah, it's...

35:23.702 --> 35:25.977
Can I see that? It's kind of a wife.

35:26.062 --> 35:27.381
Right there.

35:27.462 --> 35:30.613
But the Emperor of China had 1,000 ofthem.

35:32.342 --> 35:36.130
OK, like nowadays, in the West,
they have one husband for one wife.

35:36.222 --> 35:42.695
But in the olden-time cultures they had,
you know, different... different rules.

35:44.422 --> 35:46.413
Why? You feel sorry for the husband?

35:46.502 --> 35:50.575
Yeah. Can you imagine my mom
multiplied by a thousand?

35:52.022 --> 35:54.377
Creasy.

35:54.462 --> 35:56.976
- You're smiling.
- What?

35:57.062 --> 35:59.212
- You were smiling.
- No, I'm not.

35:59.302 --> 36:00.496
- You were.
- No, I was not.

36:00.582 --> 36:03.221
- You're not now, but you were.
- Youwere smiling. I wasn't.

36:03.302 --> 36:04.655
- You were.
- When?

36:04.742 --> 36:07.176
- Five seconds ago.
- I'm not smiling.

36:07.262 --> 36:11.778
- Well, a second ago you were.
- You said five seconds ago. Now that's six.

36:11.862 --> 36:13.978
- Ten seconds ago.
- Ten seconds ago I was smiling.

36:14.062 --> 36:17.975
OK, in the next ten seconds,
we'll see who smiles first.

36:21.302 --> 36:23.691
- You smiled already. See? You did.
- You.

36:23.782 --> 36:26.171
No, that wasn't a... That was a smirk.

36:26.262 --> 36:31.734
That's not a smile. A smirk is different. They
both start with S, but they're not the same...

36:31.822 --> 36:34.495
- Do your homework.
- You were.

36:37.422 --> 36:39.219
Bang!

36:40.142 --> 36:42.702
Stop, stop, stop.
Come back, come back.

36:42.782 --> 36:44.010
Bang!

36:45.582 --> 36:47.413
Stop, stop, stop, stop, stop, stop.

36:47.502 --> 36:50.778
Come here. Hurry up, hurry up.

36:50.862 --> 36:52.454
Set.

36:52.542 --> 36:54.931
Bang! Bang!

36:57.982 --> 37:02.180
You don't flinch when you hear
the gunshot, understand?

37:02.262 --> 37:07.256
Listen for the sound. You don't anticipate.
Concentrate on the sound. Understand me?

37:07.342 --> 37:09.333
They're gaining on you. Go, go, go, go!

37:09.422 --> 37:13.620
Stop, stop! Come on, get out. Let's go again.

37:28.702 --> 37:32.092
?Yqué? ?Todo bien?
Las maletas, porfavor.

37:32.182 --> 37:33.615
- Daddy!
- Come here, girl.

37:35.062 --> 37:38.054
- I missed you so much.
- I missed you.

37:38.142 --> 37:41.214
I got a surprise for you. Are you ready?

37:41.742 --> 37:43.733
You got me a dog! You got me a dog!

37:44.382 --> 37:47.180
- You bought me a dog! Oh, my gosh!
- What do you think?

37:47.262 --> 37:50.618
Oh, my gosh.
Just what I wanted. What's his name?

37:50.702 --> 37:53.580
- Sam. Like Dad.
- Come on, Sam! Come on, Sam!

37:55.142 --> 37:57.133
State...

37:59.502 --> 38:02.255
Bhutan. It's a Himalayan kingdom.

38:02.342 --> 38:05.778
They were having some problems
with the royal family not long ago.

38:05.862 --> 38:07.500
OK.

38:09.302 --> 38:11.657
Any more questions?

38:11.742 --> 38:16.816
- Do you have a girlfriend, Creasy?
- What? No. What kind of question is that?

38:16.902 --> 38:20.053
- You're supposed to be studying history.
- It's Creasy history.

38:20.142 --> 38:22.940
- No, ancient history.
- Who was your very first girlfriend?

38:23.022 --> 38:24.091
- Nonya.
- Nonya?

38:24.182 --> 38:27.492
Nonya business, that's who. OK?

38:28.182 --> 38:30.059
Hi.

38:30.142 --> 38:33.691
Tomorrow after you drop off Pita,
could you take me to get my hair done?

38:33.782 --> 38:35.773
Yes, ma'am.

38:35.862 --> 38:38.740
All right. Well, I'll...

38:38.822 --> 38:41.416
I'll leave you to your history.

38:41.502 --> 38:44.300
- Good night.
- Good night, honey.

38:46.542 --> 38:49.010
- OK, now ask me.
- Ask you what?

38:55.142 --> 38:58.100
Go, Pita! Go, go, go, go, go!

38:58.182 --> 39:00.093
!Ràpido!!Ràpido!

39:00.182 --> 39:02.571
Go, go, go, go, go!

39:02.662 --> 39:04.937
!Bravo, Pita!

39:06.142 --> 39:08.292
- 10.99.
- Yes!

39:11.462 --> 39:13.930
- I'm tough, Creasy.
- No such thing as tough.

39:14.022 --> 39:17.253
There's trained and there's untrained.
Now, which are you?

39:17.342 --> 39:20.652
- Trained.
- Trained. OK, we'll go again.

39:28.662 --> 39:30.653
- Here.
- Stand here near the finish line.

39:30.742 --> 39:32.300
OK. Hey.

39:32.382 --> 39:35.454
I'm a prisoner in the block
until the gunshot sets me free.

39:35.542 --> 39:39.296
That's right. Don't smile, don't fool around
ifyou wanna win. Trained or untrained?

39:39.382 --> 39:40.974
- Trained.
- Go.

39:41.982 --> 39:46.498
- Señor Creasy, nice to see you.
- Good to see you, Madre.

39:46.582 --> 39:49.142
Pita's parents are away on business in Juàrez.

39:49.222 --> 39:51.782
Today, you are her father.

41:11.142 --> 41:13.610
!Yla ganadora es Pita Ramos!

41:19.062 --> 41:22.099
I won, Creasy! I won!

41:22.182 --> 41:24.571
- OK.
- I won!

41:34.462 --> 41:38.774
- Once upon a time, when we were young...
- When lwas young.

41:38.862 --> 41:41.740
Well, when we were young
and he was younger,

41:41.822 --> 41:44.575
and all heads turned our way,

41:44.662 --> 41:47.176
we made a deal to take the world together.

41:47.262 --> 41:51.050
Yeah, then one day I got a call,
and you said...

41:51.142 --> 41:54.418
"I'm in love, I'm in love!"

41:54.502 --> 41:56.857
"And I'm movin' to Mexico!"

41:56.942 --> 41:59.376
And I said, "Huh?"

41:59.462 --> 42:02.852
I said, "What happened to the plan?
What happened to it?"

42:02.942 --> 42:07.572
- I said, "The plan's right here!"
- Yeah, yeah. And what'd I do?

42:07.662 --> 42:09.892
I hung up. And then I met Alicia.

42:09.982 --> 42:14.100
And then I went, "Now I got ya. I got ya."

42:14.182 --> 42:16.855
I got it. Can I kiss her?

42:16.942 --> 42:18.853
Absolutely.

42:18.942 --> 42:21.581
Hey, what are you doin'?

42:25.862 --> 42:30.378
- You got me.
- OK, I think now's as good a time as any.

42:33.102 --> 42:35.741
I bought it with my own money.

42:37.582 --> 42:39.573
Thank you.

42:41.102 --> 42:43.093
Open it.

42:47.262 --> 42:51.653
It's Saint Jude, the patron saint of lost causes.

42:55.302 --> 42:57.213
Well deserved.

43:01.102 --> 43:03.775
Thank you, Pita. It's beautiful.

43:05.182 --> 43:07.173
You're welcome.

43:54.502 --> 43:56.458
- Dad?
- Yes, sweetie?

43:56.542 --> 43:59.010
- Can I talk to you?
- Yes.

44:00.582 --> 44:03.494
I don't wanna play piano, I wanna swim.

44:03.582 --> 44:07.734
It's not open for discussion, honey, OK?
Mr Lozzi's a very, very famous teacher.

44:07.822 --> 44:11.974
If he accepts you as a student,
you're gonna play the piano. Sorry.

44:12.062 --> 44:13.939
- Whatever.
- Baby.

44:16.382 --> 44:18.896
- I love you.
- Love you.

44:18.982 --> 44:22.099
- I just want what's best for you, you know?
- OK.

44:22.182 --> 44:24.332
OK, honey.

44:34.102 --> 44:36.775
Ifyou broke all my fingers,
then taped them back together,

44:36.862 --> 44:39.615
I wouldn't be able to play piano,
but I could still swim.

44:39.702 --> 44:41.897
Sam, get back.

44:41.982 --> 44:44.860
Don't be a crybaby.
You're tougher than that.

44:44.942 --> 44:46.933
Sit, sit, sit, sit, sit, sit.

44:50.062 --> 44:52.496
Remember the day you wanted the pencil?

44:52.582 --> 44:55.619
- Yeah.
- I know why.

44:55.702 --> 44:57.181
Yeah?

44:57.262 --> 45:01.733
You wanted the licence number off ofthat car.
I wrote it down in my notebook.

45:01.822 --> 45:04.382
I got it all but the last number.

45:04.462 --> 45:07.579
I'll get it from you later. Can you belch?

45:07.662 --> 45:09.812
Like burp. Can you burp?

45:13.902 --> 45:18.339
- That's good. That's very good.
- I just had a Coke.

45:18.422 --> 45:20.697
Listen to me. This famous teacher...

45:20.782 --> 45:24.695
He teaches a lot of rich kids and plays
for the symphonies and all that, right?

45:24.782 --> 45:27.342
Belch every few minutes
while you're practising.

45:27.422 --> 45:32.052
You apologise to him, but you keep belching.
You'll offend every sensibility he has.

45:32.142 --> 45:35.691
Very good. You'll be back in the pool
in 24 hours, I guarantee you.

45:35.782 --> 45:37.773
Right, Sam?

45:42.942 --> 45:46.537
- Hola.
- Lupita Ramos.

45:49.582 --> 45:51.652
For you, Creasy.

45:54.782 --> 45:56.579
Thank you.

45:59.742 --> 46:02.939
- How does this look?
- Good. Good.

46:05.342 --> 46:07.014
- Hola, Pita.
- Hola.

46:07.502 --> 46:08.139
Come on in.

46:08.222 --> 46:09.211
Bye.

46:09.302 --> 46:11.293
- How long?
- One hour.

46:11.382 --> 46:13.179
Gracias.

46:39.942 --> 46:41.534
Pita...

46:49.662 --> 46:52.734
!Pita! Porfavor, concéntrate.

48:11.782 --> 48:12.817
Pita!

48:15.462 --> 48:16.292
Pita!

48:23.262 --> 48:24.934
No te vas a callar.

48:25.982 --> 48:27.938
Pita!

48:36.542 --> 48:38.134
Run!

49:53.622 --> 49:55.977
Creasy!

49:56.062 --> 49:57.973
Creasy!

50:00.022 --> 50:02.172
Creasy. Creasy!

50:03.022 --> 50:05.058
Creasy!

50:16.942 --> 50:18.421
I can't...

50:40.582 --> 50:45.098
John W Creasy is under arrest for the murder
oftwo officers ofthe Judicial Police.

50:45.182 --> 50:47.776
Creasy!

50:56.022 --> 50:59.537
This man, John W Creasy,

50:59.622 --> 51:01.180
an American citizen,

51:01.262 --> 51:02.980
is under arrest for the murder

51:03.222 --> 51:05.577
oftwo officers ofthe Judicial Police

51:08.142 --> 51:10.702
and is suspected of possible involvement

51:10.782 --> 51:13.421
in the kidnapping of Lupita Martin Ramos.

51:15.502 --> 51:18.062
Chief Ramirez...

51:20.142 --> 51:22.576
The two officers who were killed.

51:22.662 --> 51:24.937
Records show they were off duty at the time.

51:25.622 --> 51:28.011
So why were they in uniform

51:28.302 --> 51:29.212
and in a patrol car?

51:29.302 --> 51:32.897
All I know is that they died bravely.

51:33.822 --> 51:35.016
Of course,

51:35.102 --> 51:37.696
but what exactly were they doing

51:37.782 --> 51:39.135
at the scene ofthe kidnapping?

51:39.822 --> 51:42.814
Or were they known
for their exceptional good luck?

51:42.902 --> 51:44.813
They were known for being corrupt

51:44.902 --> 51:47.257
and now are celebrated for being dead.

52:41.902 --> 52:44.257
Excuse me.

52:49.742 --> 52:51.812
Relax, OK? Relax, Sammy.

52:57.062 --> 53:00.418
I know she's your little girl. When I
tell you everything's gonna be all right,

53:00.502 --> 53:03.062
everything's gonna be all right.

53:04.662 --> 53:06.937
Señor Ramos.

53:14.622 --> 53:17.090
I'm sorry. I'm really sorry.

53:17.182 --> 53:20.811
Victor Fuentes, Anti-Kidnapping Division,
Policia Judicial.

53:20.902 --> 53:24.372
Excuse me. I'm Jordan Kalfus.
I'm the family attorney.

53:24.462 --> 53:29.616
Speak slower, please.
My Russian is better than my English.

53:29.702 --> 53:34.332
Well, I'm conducting the negotiations, and we
neither need nor want any police assistance.

53:34.422 --> 53:37.971
We're gonna handle this thing ourselves.

53:38.702 --> 53:44.937
Señor Ramos, two police officers were killed
during your daughter's abduction.

53:45.022 --> 53:47.820
I have a written order from...

53:47.982 --> 53:49.859
the Public Minister...

53:50.102 --> 53:52.013
authorising our participation...

53:52.102 --> 53:54.616
..."unofficially".

53:55.622 --> 54:00.218
Ifyou want to speak to
Attorney General Diaz, it's on me.

54:02.262 --> 54:03.900
OK.

54:03.982 --> 54:08.214
The kidnapper will tell you
to deliver the money alone.

54:08.902 --> 54:10.779
Porfavor, don't do that.

54:10.862 --> 54:16.334
Or you will find yourself in a real
Mexican hell. No mariachi, no tequila...

54:16.422 --> 54:18.413
and no Pita.

54:56.022 --> 54:57.011
Crease?

54:59.022 --> 55:00.011
Crease.

55:02.782 --> 55:06.377
When I heard it was this hospital,
I was so pleased.

55:06.462 --> 55:09.898
There is a pastry shop nearby. Delgado's.

55:09.982 --> 55:14.021
They have the best pastries in Mexico.

55:14.102 --> 55:17.890
Miguel Manzano. Director ofthe AFl.

55:17.982 --> 55:23.852
And a former director of Interpol, in Rome.

55:24.942 --> 55:28.173
- And you are?
- A friend of his. Rayburn.

55:28.262 --> 55:30.014
Rayburn.

55:43.302 --> 55:44.735
?Hola?

55:44.862 --> 55:47.456
Do you love your daughter, señor Ramos?

55:47.542 --> 55:49.578
Yes. Yes.

55:49.662 --> 55:52.734
- Do you want to see her again?
- Yes, I do.

55:52.822 --> 55:54.096
Señor...

55:55.062 --> 55:59.772
Ifyour daughter's life is
as important to you as it is to me,

55:59.862 --> 56:02.092
you will do as I say.

56:02.182 --> 56:04.138
Yes?

56:04.222 --> 56:05.701
OK, yes.

56:06.342 --> 56:08.378
Crease. You hear me?

56:11.742 --> 56:13.892
You got four of 'em, all dead.

56:15.622 --> 56:18.580
- Pita?
- It's...

56:20.382 --> 56:22.896
It's been two days.

56:22.982 --> 56:25.701
They're negotiating a ransom.

56:27.102 --> 56:30.572
These things take time, Mr Creasy.

56:34.982 --> 56:36.540
Crease.

56:38.662 --> 56:41.460
Don't fuck with me, all right?

56:46.782 --> 56:50.058
You have the ten million?
Do you have the money?

56:50.142 --> 56:53.771
- Yes, we have the money.
- Now, ifyou do as I say,

56:53.862 --> 56:58.060
the girl will be returned
exactly as she was taken.

56:58.142 --> 57:02.101
But ifyou deviate
from the process in any way...

57:02.662 --> 57:04.573
By the Virgin of Guadeloupe,

57:04.662 --> 57:07.051
I swear you will never see her again.

57:07.142 --> 57:10.134
I understand. Listen, I too
worship la Virgen de Guadalupe...

57:10.222 --> 57:12.178
I ask ifyou understand.

57:14.902 --> 57:18.019
Hello, sir. This is Mr Ramos's attorney.

57:18.102 --> 57:20.935
He's going through a very difficult time,
but he understands.

57:21.022 --> 57:24.253
Do you understand?
Repeat the drop instructions.

57:24.342 --> 57:29.291
OK, the money, ten million US, will be divided
into two 15-gallon black canvas bags,

57:29.382 --> 57:33.534
each containing five million, which
will be checked at the bank by the KR agent,

57:33.622 --> 57:38.059
then driven to the house in an armoured car,
where it will be transferred to the delivery car.

57:38.862 --> 57:41.535
You got a flat tyre here.

57:41.622 --> 57:43.613
This is for you.

57:44.662 --> 57:46.937
Hello. Yeah.

57:47.022 --> 57:49.490
Listen, I need a driver to drive Samuel.

57:49.582 --> 57:51.732
No. Why?

57:51.822 --> 57:55.497
He's got a bad ticker.
He's got a heart condition.

57:55.582 --> 57:58.654
Look, he's a nervous kid.
He doesn't respond well to stress.

58:00.702 --> 58:05.173
All right, but the car will not be powerful.

58:05.262 --> 58:10.131
Remove the trunk lid.
Use the maid's Valiant Acapulco.

58:10.862 --> 58:14.537
You will arrive at La Diana fountain at 1am.

58:14.622 --> 58:18.615
You will drive around the circle two times.

58:18.702 --> 58:23.412
Samuel will remove his shirt
and hold it out the window to ID the car.

58:23.502 --> 58:26.335
to ID the car.

58:27.382 --> 58:30.977
There is a payphone on the southeast corner.

58:31.062 --> 58:36.659
The phone will ring.
You will answer and wait for instructions.

58:36.742 --> 58:41.452
There is a map on the top
ofthe phone. Follow it.

58:43.382 --> 58:45.213
Perfecto.

58:45.302 --> 58:47.691
Tranquilo. Si.

58:49.062 --> 58:51.940
- What are you doing? He said no phones.
- Relax, relax.

58:52.022 --> 58:55.697
I'm just trying to protect your daughter, OK?

59:00.422 --> 59:01.537
What's goin' on?

59:01.862 --> 59:04.581
Hospitals can be very dangerous places,

59:04.662 --> 59:08.450
especially when you have
killed two corrupt cops.

59:20.342 --> 59:24.130
Leave the money in the trunk ofthe white car

59:24.222 --> 59:26.213
and return to your car.

59:27.942 --> 59:31.139
Do not look back.

59:39.622 --> 59:41.214
What's going on, guys?

59:41.302 --> 59:42.815
Ambush!

59:48.662 --> 59:52.337
Remember... I'm a professional.

59:52.622 --> 59:59.937
If you keep your word, I will keep mine.

01:00:08.902 --> 01:00:10.972
- Hello?
- Mr Ramos.

01:00:11.062 --> 01:00:14.452
You betrayed me. You killed my nephew.

01:00:15.062 --> 01:00:16.620
You took my money.

01:00:16.702 --> 01:00:18.613
Señor Ramos...

01:00:18.782 --> 01:00:21.535
God be with your child.

01:00:23.382 --> 01:00:28.058
All right. Get outta here, all ofyou.
Get the fuck out of my house!

01:00:28.142 --> 01:00:30.337
OK, this is Lisa...

01:00:31.182 --> 01:00:33.855
Martin Ramos. I'm Pita's mother.

01:00:35.302 --> 01:00:39.978
And I'm very sorry for whatever happened
to your nephew, but I beg you...

01:00:40.062 --> 01:00:43.020
Please don't harm my daughter.

01:00:44.662 --> 01:00:47.415
This conversation is not being recorded.

01:00:47.502 --> 01:00:49.777
You're negotiating directly with me.

01:00:49.862 --> 01:00:55.255
I'm sorry. I'm really sorry.
I wish we had talked sooner, señora.

01:00:55.342 --> 01:00:57.936
I'm really sorry.

01:00:58.622 --> 01:01:00.613
Now it is too late.

01:01:09.942 --> 01:01:14.333
Fuck off! Get the fuck out
of my fucking house! Now!

01:01:15.342 --> 01:01:17.981
Get out! Get out!

01:02:04.385 --> 01:02:07.218
Hey, Ray. How are you...?

01:02:09.465 --> 01:02:13.094
- Where am l?
- Well, it looks like a dog hospital.

01:02:17.265 --> 01:02:20.655
Manzano was afraid
the cops were gonna kill ya.

01:02:21.665 --> 01:02:23.656
How you doin', doc?

01:02:28.505 --> 01:02:30.496
What's the matter?

01:02:33.585 --> 01:02:35.780
She's dead, Crease.

01:02:38.025 --> 01:02:42.541
It's a mess. Somebody
hijacked the drop and...

01:02:46.225 --> 01:02:50.537
The kidnapper's nephew was killed,
so he killed Pita.

01:03:02.465 --> 01:03:05.935
He has gunshot wounds
